            "text": "*Orichalcum Armor*  \n*Orichalcum Shield*  \n*Orichalcum Weapon*",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "text": "|  |  |  |  |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| **Orichalcum Items** | **Hardness** | **HP** | **BT** |\n| **Thin Items** |  |\n| High-grade | 16 | 64 | 32 |\n| **Items** |  |\n| High-grade | 18 | 72 | 36 |\n| **Structure** |  |\n| High-grade | 35 | 140 | 70 |\n\n  \n*Rules for Special Materials*",
        "type": "section"
      }
    ],
    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "The most rare and valuable skymetal, orichalcum is coveted for its incredible time-related magical properties. This dull, coppery metal isn't as physically sturdy as adamantine, but orichalcum's time-bending properties protect it, granting it greater Hardness and Hit Points. If an orichalcum item takes damage but isn't destroyed, it repairs itself completely 24 hours later.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 137,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "rare"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Rare",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 131,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "b55483844b400b317f798bf6000f2f95",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Precious",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "GM Core pg. 332",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "GM Core pg. 332",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "GM Core",
            "page": 332,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Valuable materials with special properties have the precious trait. They can be substituted for base materials when you Craft items.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
